properties.name: drag
properties.description:
Which directions the container can be dragged.
Any combination of `up`, `down`, `left`, or `right`; or `none`.

properties.name: resize
properties.description:
Which edges allow resize.
Any combination of `top`, `bottom`, `left`, or `right`; or `none`.
A corner is enabled when both of its adjacent sides are enabled.

properties.name: draggable
properties.description: True if draggable in at least one direction.

properties.name: resizable
properties.description: True if resizable on at least one edge.

properties.name: minWidth
properties.description: The minium width of the content

elements.description:
`<paper-tree-node>` display a tree node with expandable/collapsible capabilities and actions menu.
A node is defined by a name, an icon and a list of actions.
Example:
    <paper-tree-node></paper-tree-node>
### Styling
The following custom properties and mixins are available for styling:
Custom property | Description | Default
----------------|-------------|----------
`--paper-tree-selected-background-color`      | Highlight color for selected node           | `rgba(200, 200, 200, 0.5)`
`--paper-tree-selected-color`                 | Text and icon color for selected node       | `inherit`
`--paper-tree-toggle-theme`                   | Change theme for node +/- toggle            |
`--paper-tree-icon-theme`                     | Change theme for node icon                  |

properties.name: items
properties.description:
Contains all the items; filled either by remote request or if no remote is given by parameter
Data hold by the root node (contains the children).

Specific item:

- `item.name`: string representing the node name.
- `item.icon`: string telling which icon to use (default to 'folder' icon).
- `item.open`: boolean telling whether the node is expanded or not.
- `item.children` array containing the children of the node.

properties.name: actions
properties.description:
`actions` available for this node. Each action object has the following fields:

- `action.label`: string representing the display name of the menu item.
- `action.event`: string which is the event name to dispatch whenever the item is clicked.

`<actindo-tree>` implements a highly reusable data tree to display your data.

### Features

- remote loading of data
- static data display
